articles.author: Jarrett Renshaw, Nidal Al-Mughrabi, Mohammad Salem
articles.description: U.S. President Joe Biden for the first time publicly vowed to withhold weapons from Israel if its forces make a major invasion of Rafah in southern Gaza while negotiations in Cairo on a ceasefire plan for the enclave were due to continue on Thursday.
articles.title: US warns Israel that Rafah invasion will jeopardise weapons supply as assault continues

articles.author: Michelle Nichols
articles.description: The United Nations General Assembly on Friday is set to back a Palestinian bid to become a full U.N. member by recognizing it as qualified to join and sending the application back to the U.N. Security Council to "reconsider the matter favorably."
articles.title: UN General Assembly set to back Palestinian bid for membership

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The Philippine national security council on Friday called for Chinese diplomats to be expelled from the country for what it called a malicious disinformation campaign that had breached local laws and diplomatic protocols.
articles.title: Philippines calls for Chinese diplomats to be expelled for disinformation

articles.author: Jennifer Rigby
articles.description: Talks to draw up a global pact to help fight future pandemics are likely to miss an initial deadline on Friday, three sources close to the process said.
articles.title: Pandemic treaty talks to the wire, likely to miss first deadline, sources say

articles.author: Jack Queen, Luc Cohen, Andy Sullivan
articles.description: Porn star Stormy Daniels will face tough questioning from Donald Trump's lawyers on Thursday as they try to dismantle the credibility of a woman whose story of a 2006 sexual encounter ultimately led to the first criminal trial of a former U.S. president.
articles.title: Stormy Daniels to face tough questions from Trump lawyers at trial

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Russian President Vladimir Putin proposed reappointing Mikhail Mishustin as prime minister, the speaker of the lower house of parliament said on Friday, keeping Putin's chief technocrat in charge of the government as Moscow presses its war in Ukraine.
articles.title: Russia's Putin proposes reappointing Mishustin as prime minister

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Russian anti-aircraft units intercepted a drone south of Moscow and there were no injuries or damage from falling debris, Moscow Mayor Sergei Sobyanin said early on Friday.
articles.title: Anti-aircraft units intercept drone south of Moscow, no damage or injuries, mayor says

articles.author: Deisy Buitrago
articles.description: Venezuela is open to paying its $10 billion debt to China, lawmaker Nicolas Maduro Guerra, son of President Nicolas Maduro, told Reuters in an interview on Thursday.
articles.title: Maduro's lawmaker son says Venezuela open to paying $10 billion debt to China

articles.author: Dan Williams
articles.description: Israelis are ready to fight with their "fingernails", Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said on Thursday in a thinly veiled rebuff to U.S. President Joe Biden's warning that arms supplies could be withheld over a planned operation in Gaza.
articles.title: Israelis ready to fight with their fingernails, Netanyahu says in veiled Biden rebuff

articles.author: Amanda Perobelli, Leonardo Benansatto
articles.description: The death toll from severe flooding in southern Brazil has risen to 107, civil defense said on Thursday, as rescue operations continued and authorities began to see the cost of recovering from the devastation in the state of Rio Grande do Sul.
articles.title: Deaths in Brazil floods rise to 107, horse rescued from rooftop
